We only need to look at the “Initial” transactions to compute the paid‐in capital. In this data the “Initial20231231001” entries are:

• Cash deposit: 3,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit: 5,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets: 8,000,000.0  

Adding these gives an initial paid‑in capital of  
  3,000,000 + 5,000,000 + 8,000,000 = 16,000,000.0

Since no further “capital injection” transactions occurred later (all other transactions are purchases, sales, expenses, etc.), the final paid‑in capital remains the same.

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Paid-in Capital Initial Value": "16000000.00",
    "Paid-in Capital End Value": "16000000.00"
  }
}
